          <p>Paddling has been a huge part of my life starting with the canoe club at age 15 at my high school in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, Canada and now working in the paddlesports industry since 1994.</p>
          <p>You will not see me paddling over waterfalls or riding the wave at the local &quot;park and play&quot; spot but my paddling adventures have taken my by canoe and kayak from my backyard in beautiful British Columbia to Angelsey in Northern Wales, to the meandering rivers of Southern Utah, northern Canada and the icy waters of Antarctica.</p>
          <p>In the last couple of years I have also spent more time Stand Up Paddle boarding and I have enjoyed experiencing the water from this new vantage point.</p>
          <p>My industry experience is varied starting in specialty retail, moving to manufacturing (I was the Sales &amp; Operations Manager at North Water Rescue &amp; Paddling Equipment for 8 years) and then as an Independent Sales Representative which I have been doing since 2005.  I was also very involved in the former, Trade Association of Paddlesports as a board member, as an Administrator and finally as the Director of the West Coast Sea Kayak Symposium for 3 years (this included its 25th anniversary year).</p>
          <p>I am also involved in my local paddlesports community volunteering as a Director with the Chilliwack Vedder River Cleanup Society.</p>

        </span><!-- ./rekman -->

