          <h3>Scott Farity <small>Vice President</small></h3>

          <span class="pull-left board-img">
            <%= image_tag( 'scott-farity.jpg', :alt => "Scott Farity", :title => "Scott Farity" ) %>
          </span>

          <p>I began my paddling life as a whitewater boater in New England in 1981.  I took up sea kayaking as a way to stay in shape for the relatively short whitewater season.  After progressing through the ACA instructor program in whitewater kayak, canoe, C-1 and sea kayak, I was still looking for additional challenges and for ways to continue to develop as a paddler and coach and that's when the BCU entered the scene.  In 1995 Nigel Dennis came to Rhode Island to run a variety or courses and I jumped on all of them.  I have been actively involved with the BCU ever since, including holding the position of  Midwest Regional Coaching Officer and member of the BCUNA Interim Board of Directors.  What I bring to the PNA Board is a depth and breadth of experience in both the ACA and BCU systems, an 18 year history of involvement with the BCU and over 30 years of multi-discipline coaching.  BCU has had a profoundly positive influence on my development as a paddler and coach and I want to help the organization to grow in the States so more paddlers can benefit from all it has to offer.</p>
          <p>Current Member of the Interim Board of Directors<br />
          Former Midwest Regional Coaching Officer<br />
          Full list of coaching qualifications at <a href="http://scottfairty.com" target="_blank">scottfairty.com</a><br />
          </p>
        </span><!-- ./farity -->

        <span class="section" id="bloyd-peshkin">
          <h3>Sharon Bloyd-Peshkin <small>Secretary</small></h3>

          <span class="pull-left board-img">
            <%= image_tag( 'sharon-bloyd-peshkin.jpg', :alt => "Sharon Bloyd-Peshkin", :title => "Sharon Bloyd-Peshkin" ) %>
          </span>

          <p>Sharon is a BCU Level 1 coach who is eagerly anticipating and preparing for her BCU Coach 2 training in June and 4-star training in July. She is also an ACA Level 4 Open Water sea kayak instructor and Level 3 Whitewater kayak instructor. She co-leads a popular weekly whitewater kayaking class at her local YMCA  coaches at a variety of symposia (WMCKA, Great Lakes, Ladies of the Lake, MEC Toronto Paddlefest, The Gales), and has been a guest coach at Adventure Crafters in Maryland and Body Boat Blade in Washington state. She is a board member of the Illinois Paddling Council and the Chicago Area Sea Kayakers Association, and has written paddling-related articles for Adventure Kayak, Sea Kayaker and Ocean Paddler magazines. With her husband, Alec (Midwest RCO), she maintains the blog Have Kayaks, Will Travel (<a href="http://bloyd-peshkin.blogspot.com" target="_blank">bloyd-peshkin.blogspot.com</a>). She is a team paddler for Snap Dragon Design, Werner and Valley. Sharon says the BCU has made her a better coach because its programs are grounded in research about how to help people gain skills and reach their paddling goals. She is eager to do what she can to help promote BCU training for coaches and paddlers and make it more widely available, whether that means bring on the board or assisting those who are.</p>
        </span><!-- ./bloyd-peshkin -->

        <span class="section" id="ozard">
          <h3>John Ozard <small>Treasurer</small></h3>

          <span class="pull-left board-img">
            <%= image_tag( 'john-ozard.jpg', :alt => "John Ozard", :title => "John Ozard" ) %>
          </span>

          <p>John Ozard is a Certified Wildlife Biologist, and is currently Leader of the Wildlife Diversity Unit in the Division of Fish, Wildlife and Marine Resources of the New York State Department of Environmental Conservation. He has worked in the nongame wildlife and endangered species program areas throughout his 37 year career.</p>
          <p>John is an avid outdoorsman and paddler. His interest in canoeing began over 40 years ago, and includes leading wilderness river trips in the 1970s. In the early 1980s he built a 16 foot redwood strip tandem canoe. In late 2003 he discovered sea kayaking and was instantly hooked. John has been a member of the American Canoe Association (ACA) and the British Canoe Union (BCU) since 2005. He has pursued advanced training from the BCU and holds a 2 Star Paddlesport award, a 3 Star Sea Kayak award, a 4 Star Sea Kayak Leader award, and a 3 Star Open Canoe award. He has also completed the BCU&apos;s Coastal Navigation and Tidal Planning course, Foundation Safety and Rescue Training, and 4 Star Open Canoe Leader training. John is a Level 1 UKCC (BCU) Coach and is a Level 2 Coach aspirant.</p>
          <p>As a Director of Paddlesports North America, John brings a wealth of experience to the Board. He currently manages a staff of 12 biologists and technicians in the Wildlife Diversity Unit, and has served on the Board of Directors of Old Songs, Inc. since 1981. Old Songs, Inc. is an educational, not-for-profit corporation dedicated to preserving traditional music and dance. John currently serves as Treasurer of Old Songs, and has previously served as President and Vice-President. In his current role he oversees revenues and assets totaling approximately $294,000.  John is also the Director of Grounds for the annual Old Songs Festival of Traditional Music and Dance, now in its 34th year. In this role he manages the on-site operation of the event, including setup and cleanup.</p>
        </span><!-- ./ozard -->

