          <p>Steve has worked as an outdoor educator since 1987 when he started kayaking on remote sea lochs in North West Scotland. Since then he has paddled, guided and coached extensively in the United Kingdom, and throughout Europe and North America.</p>
          <p>Steve is a full time paddle sport coach involved with training and certification of personal skills, leadership and coaching qualifications at all levels and in multiple disciplines.</p>
          <p>He is currently the head paddle sports instructor for the  <a href="http://www.plattsburgh.edu/academics/exp/expoverview.php" target="_blank">Expeditionary Studies</a> Major at SUNY Plattsburgh and in his spare time presents at kayak symposiums and organizes/works on BCU star and coach courses.</p>
          <p>Steve holds qualifications in many adventure sports, including sea kayaking certifications at the highest level from the British Canoe Union (Level 5 Coach Sea and Level 5 Assessor Sea, Coach Level 1 and 2 tutor) and American Canoe Association (Advanced Open Water Instructor).</p>
          <p>Steve enjoys nothing more than helping people improve their understanding of technique and environment to make stronger safer paddlers.</p>
        </span><!-- ./maynard -->

        <span class="section" id="franklin">
