          <p>Shawna Franklin has been involved in paddle sports for over two decades. Shawna is a co-owner of the two time award winning kayak school <a href="http://bodyboatblade.com" target="_blank">Body Boat Blade International</a>. Shawna is a lead coach and peer-reviewed coach educator.  Shawna is a team athlete for top paddle sports manufacturers and has worked with some to create award winning products. She has been featured in magazines, films and has taught as a guest coach at symposiums worldwide. Shawna is currently a BCU Coach Level 5 aspirant, BCU 5 Star Sea Leader, BCU FSRT provider, and BCU Assessor Grade 4. She also holds the BCU 4 Star award in surf and whitewater and the BCU Canoe 2 Star award. Shawna has been an active member in the BCU since 1999.  Her most notable personal paddling accomplishments are a successful circumnavigation of Iceland in 2003, circumnavigation of Haida Gwaii in 2008, and Vancouver Island in 2011.</p>
          <p>Shawna brings a good blend of energy and expertise to the PNA Board.  She brings 19 years successful business experience, extensive knowledge and experience of paddle sport, and a long history and experience with the BCU. Her leadership and education skills are invaluable when working with others on the board. Shawna is a life time artist and can also offer graphic and design expertise to the job. Shawna is a committed and passionate paddler and coach in the paddling disciplines of sea kayaking, canoeing, kayak surfing, race kayaks and stand up paddle boarding.</p>
          <p>Shawna believes strongly in the mission and the goals of PNA. She is thrilled to be part of the process that will allow this organization to grow and to flourish and continue making unique opportunities available for new paddlers and experienced paddlers alike in their development and aspirations.</p>
